-- Credit Suisse Hires Barclays’s Aldridge to Head Sales Group
-- B y   T a y l o r   T e p p e r
-- 2013-01-15T20:23:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/credit-suisse-hires-barclays-s-aldridge-to-head-sales-group.html
Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  hired Steve Aldridge as head of global currencies and emerging-markets
electronic sales in Europe, Middle East and Africa.  The former head of  Barclays Plc’s (BARC)  electronic foreign-
exchange sales for the U.K., Middle East and Northern Europe,
Aldridge will report to the Zurich-based bank’s global head of
fixed-income electronic sales, Rob Maher, according to spokesman
Adam Bradbery.  Aldridge joined Credit Suisse’s London office at the start
of last week. He succeeds Jonathan Wykes, who joined Bank of
America Corp. in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
